changelist.name: New AppDb Methods
changelist.comment: New AppDb Methods - Implemented getRestaurantTimeStampFromList - Implemented getRestaurantTimeStampsFromList

task.summary: New AppDb Methods - Implemented getRestaurantTimeStampFromList - Implemented getRestaurantTimeStampsFromList - Implemented Test Drivers for the aforementioned methods
Some progress on the result page.
minRating gets passed to the result page
Added rating stars to Result Page (with Anthony's help)
Some fine-tuning for star rating on Result Page
Implement Sosnick's changes More work on coloring action bars
Prettied up result page Stars are broken, and that's okay.
Some work on stars. Still broken -- getting there.
Finished stars
No result image is handled Splash screen Yelp logo update again
Cleaning up User Preferences
More User Preferences Cleanup Removed a lot of "Red List" references.
Removed splash screen load time correction. Splash screen wasn't always being displayed.
Results Page Selector is randomizing results
Results Page Yellow button pushes the correct restaurant into database
Fixed result page synchronization issues
RedListed restaurants no longer showing

Restaurant Selector Demo available in Settings - Deleted RestaurantTestActivity (it no longer works) - Deleted RestaurantSelectorTestActivity (outdated and it can overwrite contents of the lists) - Restaurant class initializes member variable weight to -1 (flag for no weight assigned) - TODO: It says timestamp of a yellow-listed restaurant should affect the weight linearly with the length of time between timestamp and now, but this hasn't been implemented yet.
When user returns from green button intent, they're in MainActivity. This operates under our assumption that when user presses the green button, they've committed to the restaurant.

Began logic for green followup, reorganized ResultPageActivity - ResultPageActivity: placed activity lifecycle methods together, background tasks together, etc. - Toast in OnResume() of MainActivity will be replaced with a dialog - TODO: Dialog asks user if they liked the restaurant. If so, restaurant remains in green list; if not, place in red list instead

Restaurant Selector Demo available in Settings - Deleted RestaurantTestActivity (it no longer works) - Deleted RestaurantSelectorTestActivity (outdated and it can overwrite contents of the lists) - TODO: It says timestamp of a yellow-listed restaurant should affect the weight linearly with the length of time between timestamp and now, but this hasn't been implemented yet.
